China Sets Regional Energy-Saving Targets, 21st Century Herald Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-16T01:22:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/china-sets-regional-energy-saving-targets-21st-century-herald-reports.html
  China  is starting to set specific
energy-saving goals for different regions to cut energy use per
unit of gross domestic unit by a range of 10 percent to 18
percent between 2010 and 2015, the 21st Century Business Herald
reported today, citing an unidentified person close to the
National Development and Reform Commission.  The country is setting an 18 percent energy-saving target
for the cities of Shanghai and Tianjin and the provinces of
Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Guangdong, the report said. The city of
Beijing and the provinces of Hebei, Liaoning and Shandong are
asked to cut energy use by 17 percent, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  